s/application/src/spec_contracts.rs` (lines 209-260)\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY TYPES/STRUCTS/ENUMS/TRAITS\n\n```rust\n// Phase Enum (5 variants in addition to state machine)\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum UltraplanPhase {\n    Idle,\n    Launching,\n    Polling,\n    AwaitingInput,\n    Approved,\n    Stopping,\n    Completed,\n    Failed,\n}\n\n// Session State\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct UltraplanSession {\n    pub session_id: String,\n    pub phase: UltraplanPhase,\n}\n\n// Policy Configuration\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]\npub struct UltraplanPolicy {\n    pub single_active_session: bool,\n}\n\n// Error Types\n#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]\npub enum UltraplanError {\n    #[error(\"disabled by policy\")]\n    DisabledByPolicy,\n    #[error(\"already active\")]\n    AlreadyActive,\n    #[error(\"launch failed\")]\n    LaunchFailed,\n    #[error(\"poll timeout\")]\n    PollTimeout,\n    #[error(\"approval failed\")]\n    ApprovalFailed,\n    #[error(\"archive failed\")]\n    ArchiveFailed,\n    #[error(\"transport error: {0}\")]\n    Transport(String),\n}\n\n// Main Service Trait\n#[async_trait]\npub trait UltraplanService: Send + Sync {\n    async fn launch(&self, prompt: &str, policy: UltraplanPolicy) \n        -> Result<UltraplanSession, UltraplanError>;\n    async fn poll(&self, session_id: &str) \n        -> Result<UltraplanPhase, UltraplanError>;\n    async fn stop(&self, session_id: &str) \n        -> Result<(), UltraplanError>;\n    async fn archive_orphan(&self, session_id: &str) \n        -> Result<(), UltraplanError>;\n}\n\n// Runtime Trait (internal abstraction)\n#[async_trait]\npub trait UltraplanRuntime: Send + Sync {\n    async fn launch_session(&self, prompt: &str) \n        -> Result<String, UltraplanError>;\n    async fn poll_phase(&self, session_id: &str) \n        -> Result<UltraplanPhase, UltraplanError>;\n    async fn stop_session(&self, session_id: &str) \n        -> Result<(), UltraplanError>;\n    async fn archive_session(&self, session_id: &str) \n        -> Result<(), UltraplanError>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. DEFAULT IMPLEMENTATION\n\n**DefaultUltraplanService<R>** provides:\n- **Local state management:** Mutex-based state tracking with ActiveSession and revision counter\n- **Transition validation:** Static method `transition_allowed()` enforces state machine graph\n- **Keyword routing:** Auto-detects \"ultraplan\" keyword with guards\n- **Orphan prevention:** Automatic archive on failure paths\n- **Terminal state detection:** Clears active markers for terminal states (Completed, Failed)\n- **Concurrency protection:** Revision-based optimistic locking for poll operations\n\n---\n\n## 5. EXISTING TEST FILES\n\n**Status:** No dedicated acceptance test file yet (but infrastructure in place)\n\n**Related Test Files in Project:**\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/kairos_acceptance_tests.rs` (697 lines)\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/bridge_mode_acceptance_tests.rs` (352 lines)\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/coordinator_mode_acceptance_tests.rs` (537 lines)\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/multi_agent_orchestration_acceptance_tests.rs` (561 lines)\n\n**Tests within ultraplan_service.rs:** 770 lines total with embedded unit/integration tests\n\n---\n\n## 6. TEST PATTERNS USED IN PROJECT\n\n### A. **Test Organization Structure**\n- Test modules embedded in source files with `#[cfg(test)] mod tests { ... }`\n- Acceptance test modules named `*_acceptance_tests.rs` with doc comments explaining contract coverage\n- Section markers (§) to cross-reference contract sections\n- Helper functions at module start for setup\n\n### B. **Mock/Double Pattern**\n```rust\n// VecDeque-based result queuing for sequential assertions\n#[derive(Default)]\nstruct Mock<T> {\n    results: Arc<Mutex<VecDeque<Result<T, Error>>>>,\n    calls: Arc<Mutex<Vec<String>>>,\n}\n\n// Trait impl pops results in order\n#[async_trait]\nimpl Trait for Mock<T> {\n    async fn operation(&self) -> Result<T, Error> {\n        self.results.lock().await.pop_front()\n            .expect(\"missing result\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### C. **Test Naming Conventions**\n- `contract_*` - Unit/contract invariant tests\n- `integration_*` - Multi-step workflow tests  \n- `*_returns_*_when_*` - Behavior specifications\n- Descriptive names with `assert_*` helpers\n\n### D. **Concurrency Testing Pattern**\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn concurrent_operation_is_guarded() {\n    let svc = Arc::new(Service::new(...));\n    let (a, b) = tokio::join!(\n        svc.launch(...),\n        svc.launch(...)\n    );\n    // Race condition assertions\n}\n```\n\n### E. **Test Double Patterns**\n- Mock implementations with builder methods: `.with_results()`, `.for_happy_path()`\n- Notification channels (Arc<Notify>) for race condition testing\n- Queued results with `expect()` for debugging missing mocks\n\n### F. **Acceptance Test Template**\n```rust\n/// <Feature> acceptance tests (US-NNN)\n///\n/// Covers all scenarios from <contract>.md §N Acceptance Matrix:\n///   §N.1 Contract tests – <invariant descriptions>\n///   §N.2 Integration tests – <workflow descriptions>\n///   §N.3 CLI behaviour tests – <command patterns>\nuse crate::{ /* imports from spec_contracts */ };\n\n// Helper functions for context setup\nfn test_context() -> Context { /* ... */ }\n\n// §N.1 Contract tests\n#[test]\nfn contract_invariant_holds() { /* ... */ }\n\n// §N.2 Integration tests\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn integration_workflow_succeeds() { /* ... */ }\n\n// §N.3 CLI behaviour tests\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn cli_command_produces_expected_output() { /* ... */ }\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n**Workspace Layout:**\n```\n/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/\n├── Cargo.toml (workspace)\n├── docs/\n│   └── ultraplan-contract.md\n├── crates/\n│   ├── application/\n│   │   ├── Cargo.toml\n│   │   └── src/\n│   │       ├── spec_contracts.rs (trait definitions)\n│   │       ├── ultraplan_service.rs (implementation + 29 unit tests)\n│   │       ├── lib.rs (module declarations)\n│   │       ├── *_acceptance_tests.rs (7 test modules)\n│   │       └── *_service.rs (other services)\n│   ├── domain/\n│   ├── ports/\n│   ├── config/\n│   ├── remote-runtime/\n│   ├── platform/\n│   ├── mcp-runtime/\n│   ├── bootstrap/\n│   │   └── tests/\n│   │       └── spec_governance_gate.rs (validates contracts)\n│   └── cli/\n├── tasks/\n└── .ralph-tui/\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. ULTRAPLAN SERVICE IMPLEMENTATION HIGHLIGHTS\n\n**Features:**\n- Single-active-session policy enforcement\n- Transition graph validation (18 allowed transitions defined)\n- Keyword auto-routing (\"/ultraplan\" detection)\n- Orphan session archival on failure\n- Active session marker tracking with revision counter\n- Approved→Completed automatic state resolution\n- Race condition protection via revision-based optimistic locking\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- Policy disabled detection\n- Concurrency guard returns `AlreadyActive`\n- Downstream failures trigger archive attempts\n- Stop clears state before returning errors\n\n---\n\n## 9. TESTING MATRIX FROM CONTRACT\n\nThe contract specifies (but tests not yet implemented):\n\n**9.1 Contract Tests:**\n- Invalid phase transition rejected\n- Concurrent launch returns `AlreadyActive`\n- Stop/cleanup deterministic from active state\n\n**9.2 Integration Tests:**\n- Launch → Poll → Approved → Completed happy path\n- Launch success + downstream failure archives\n- Poll timeout returns `PollTimeout`\n\n**9.3 CLI Behavior Tests:**\n- Bare command returns guidance\n- Keyword-trigger while active doesn't re-launch\n- Stop clears markers and session URL\n\n**Note:** The ultraplan_service.rs file contains 29 unit/integration tests covering these scenarios but lacks a formal `ultraplan_acceptance_tests.rs` file following the project's pattern."}],"totalDurationMs